events.name: Workshop: Introduction to Docker and Kubernetes
events.description:
• What we'll do
Docker and Kubernetes are changing the way we configure our server and deployments. Be it your local environment setup, your CI pipeline or your massive production cluster - these two technologies make it easier and more manageable to setup and deploy. This hands on workshop is all about what these technologies are about and how they will help you setup and deploy your next product!

This workshop will be delivered by Technical Lead at 10Pearls Mohammad Umair Ali Khan and Technical Lead at Recurship and Google Developer Expert Mashhood Rastgar who are both using these technologies in their respective organizations.

• What to bring
Laptops

events.name: Mobile Sites Certification - FAST

venue.name: FAST - National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences
venue.address_1: ST-4 Sector 17-D, On National Highway, Karachi

events.description:
• What we'll do
People often find it easier to learn together rather than do pure self study. ACM – NUCES with collaboration of GDG Kolachi is going to organize a one day event for FASTIANS in order to equip them with the skills required to build next generation mobile sites, and get certified.

The event will be approximately 3-4 hours long. During the first half of the event, Pakistan's first technical Google Developer Expert along with other industry experts will introduce concepts related to mobile sites and the study materials necessary to pass the certification. After that, students will attempt multiple choice questions based exam, and instantly get certified. Google Developer Groups (GDGs) are for developers who are interested in Google's developer technology; everything from the Android, Chrome, Drive and Google Cloud platforms, to product APIs like the Cast API, Maps API, and Youtube API. The local chapter of Google Developers Group in Karachi is called GDG Kolachi, you can find more about their activity here: https://www.facebook.com/GDGKolachi/
https://www.facebook.com/acmnuces/inbox/

Register Yourself Now at:
https://goo.gl/forms/OqPHBOLDpeRqC74M2
Registration Deadline 9th February!!!

*Limited Seats Available
**Only For Seniors & Juniors of FAST-NUCES

events.name: Women Techmakers - Speak to Lead
events.description:
Do you think you have stage fright or lack the confidence to present on stage? Do you ever feel that you are just mumbling during a presentation while the audience stares at you? Or maybe, you want to say a lot about something on stage but you’re unable to?

If so, this event is for you!

GDG Kolachi brings you 'Women Techmakers - Speak to Lead', an event where women from various backgrounds will gather to fight their stage fright and polish their public speaking skills under mentors and facilitators! Speak to Lead is a half-day event that consists of speaker sessions and a public speaking training workshop hosted by OpenMic. Participants will be trained to tell their stories on stage and communicate in a better way.

Join us to speak!

The event is primarily for females and FREE but we have limited seats, so register now!

Register at: https://forms.gle/qLAfKnkvCAKnQB5s9

events.name: Managing Time and Mental Health while WFH amidst COVID-19
events.description:
Due to the Corona outbreak around the globe, most companies have shifted to work from home completely. Working from home (WFH) requires commitment and dedication on a whole new level. As we aren't habitual of WFH, we don't really know how to manage work, family and health together all at once.

Women Techmakers Kolachi and GDG Kolachi in collaboration with NIC Karachi present a virtual meetup on managing work from home more effectively.

The meetup will include three different live sessions hosted by professionals who have experience working from home that will help you have a better idea of how to manage things more easily!

Join us on 4th April, 4:00 - 5:30 PM and RSVP to “Going” for on our events on

Zoom:

upcoming.name: #IamRemarkable Online Workshop
upcoming.description:
#IamRemarkable is a Google Initiative for empowering women and underrepresented groups by encouraging them to celebrate their achievements in the workplace and beyond.
Research shows that people who celebrate and self-promote their achievements tend to be more positive and successful in life.
The aim of #IamRemarkable is to encourage celebration of achievements by helping improve the self-promotion tactics and motivation of women in the workplace and beyond.

Venue: Register on the following link to get an invitation for the workshop https://bit.ly/3bORhJN
